    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_buwat" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d4387e66" type="lemma"><orth>buwat</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d4387e69"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>место</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>place</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Обе формы, %ibuwat%i и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bynat"/>,
                    получились из *%ibyn%i-%iwat%i | %ibun%i-%iwat%i, собственно „нижнее (%ibun%i)
                    место (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_wat"/>). В одном случае выпал носовой
                    (%ibunwat%i → %ibuwat%i), как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kwaʒæn"/> (из
                    %ikomwaʒæn%i) ‘разговенье’ или в %istawat%i (отложилось в балкарском) из
                    *%istanwat%i, см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_stonwat"/> ‘загон’, в другом
                    полугласный %iw%i (%ibynwat%i → %ibynat%i), как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fadat"/> (из %ifadwat%i) ‘возможность’ и др. Вариант
                    %ibuwat%i в форме %ibawat, bavat, buvat%i обильно отложился в балкарской
                    топонимике: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e92" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>Nal-bawat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e97" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w>Ʒel-bawat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e100" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w>Sas-bawat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e103" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w>Xunux-bawat</w></mentioned> и другие названия урочищ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>284</biblScope></bibl>).
                    Вероятно, из осетинского же идет <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e110" xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>buott</w>
                        <gloss><q>футляр</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e119" xml:lang="inh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ножны</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e125" xml:lang="inh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>переплет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e131" xml:lang="inh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>конверт</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Генко</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЗКВ"/><biblScope>V 719</biblScope></bibl>). Ср.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bynat"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Both forms, %ibuwat%i and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bynat"/>, are derivated from *%ibyn%i-%iwat%i | %ibun%i-%iwat%i, in fact "lower
                    (%ibun%i) place (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_wat"/>)". In one case a nazal
                    consonant has been lost (%ibunwat%i → %ibuwat%i), like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kwaʒæn"/> (from %ikomwaʒæn%i) ‘first meal after fast’ or in
                    %istawat%i (found in Balkar) from *%istanwat%i, see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_stonwat"/> ‘fold’, in the other case a semi-vowel %iw%i has
                    been lost (%ibynwat%i → %ibynat%i), like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fadat"/> (from %ifadwat%i) ‘possibility’ etc. The variant %ibuwat%i in the forms
                    %ibawat, bavat, buvat%i is widespread in Balkar toponyms: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e158" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>Nal-bawat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e163" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w>Ʒel-bawat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e166" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w>Sas-bawat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e169" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w>Xunux-bawat</w></mentioned> and other mountain areas' names
                            (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>284</biblScope></bibl>). Probably, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e176" xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>buott</w>
                        <gloss><q>case</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e185" xml:lang="inh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>sheath</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e191" xml:lang="inh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>cover</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d4387e197" xml:lang="inh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>envelope</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Генко</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЗКВ"/><biblScope>V 719</biblScope></bibl>)
                    comes from Ossetic. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bynat"/>.</etym>
